{
  "Protein Synthesis": "蛋白质合成",
  "This lesson covers the fundamental measures of center used to analyze and summarize data sets. You'll learn how to calculate and apply the mean, median, and mode, and understand when each is most appropriate.": "这个课程涵盖了分析和总结数据集的中心的基本测量方法。 您将学会如何计算和应用平均值、 中位数和模式, 并了解何时最合适 。",
  "What is eutrophication?": "什么是富营养化?",
  "Eutrophication occurs when excess nutrients — mainly nitrogen and phosphorus from agricultural runoff, sewage, or industrial discharge — enter a body of water. These nutrients fuel rapid algal growth (blooms). When the algae die, decomposing bacteria consume dissolved oxygen, creating hypoxic 'dead zones' where fish and other aquatic organisms cannot survive.": "富营养化发生于过剩的营养物质——主要是农业径流、污水或工业排放的氮和磷——进入水体时,这些营养物质会加速藻类的快速生长(Bluoms),在藻类死亡时,分解的细菌会消耗溶解的氧气,在鱼类和其他水生生物无法存活的地区形成缺氧的“死区”。",
  "What is biomagnification?": "什么是生物放大?",
  "Biomagnification is the increasing concentration of a persistent, fat-soluble substance (such as DDT or mercury) at each higher trophic level. Organisms at the top of the food chain — like eagles or tuna — can accumulate toxin concentrations millions of times greater than those found in the surrounding water.": "生物放大作用是指一种持久性、可脂肪溶性物质(如滴滴涕或汞)在较高营养级的浓度日益提高,食物链顶端的生物——如鹰或金枪鱼——可能积累的毒素浓度比周围水中的浓度高出数百万倍。",
  "What is a biological indicator (bioindicator)?": "什么是生物指标(生物指标)?",
  "A bioindicator is a living organism used to assess the quality of an environment. For example, lichens indicate air quality (they die when sulfur dioxide is high), mayfly larvae indicate clean water, and amphibian declines signal habitat degradation. Their sensitivity to pollutants makes them natural early-warning systems.": "生物指标是一种用于评估环境质量的生物体,例如,地衣显示空气质量(当二氧化硫含量高时死亡)、幼虫显示清洁水、两栖降低生境退化信号,对污染物的敏感度使它们成为自然预警系统。",
  "What is carbon sequestration?": "什么是碳固存?",
  "Carbon sequestration is the process of capturing atmospheric CO₂ and storing it long-term. Natural sinks include forests (trees store carbon in biomass), oceans, wetlands, and soil. Geological sequestration involves injecting CO₂ underground. Forests globally sequester about 2.6 billion tons of CO₂ per year.": "碳固存是捕捉和长期储存大气二氧化碳的过程,自然汇包括森林(树木在生物量中储存碳)、海洋、湿地和土壤,地质固存涉及地下注入二氧化碳,全球森林每年封存约26亿吨二氧化碳。",
  "What is bioremediation?": "什么是生物补救?",
  "Bioremediation uses microorganisms, plants, or fungi to detoxify or remove pollutants from contaminated environments. For example, oil-eating bacteria can break down petroleum hydrocarbons after a spill, and sunflowers were used to absorb radioactive contaminants at Chernobyl (phytoremediation). It is cost-effective and less disruptive than chemical or mechanical cleanup.": "生物补救利用微生物、植物或真菌来解毒或清除受污染环境中的污染物,例如,食油细菌在泄漏后会分解石油碳氢化合物,向日葵被用来吸收切尔诺贝利的放射性污染物(植物补救),与化学或机械清理相比,成本效益低,破坏性小。",
  "What is an invasive species?": "什么是入侵物种?",
  "An invasive species is a non-native organism introduced (intentionally or accidentally) to an area where it lacks natural predators, diseases, or competitors. Without these checks, it reproduces rapidly and outcompetes or preys on native species, disrupting the ecosystem. Examples include Burmese pythons in the Florida Everglades and zebra mussels in the Great Lakes.": "入侵物种是一种非本地生物体(有意或无意地)引入一个没有自然掠食动物、疾病或竞争对手的地区,如果没有这些检查,它会迅速繁殖,繁殖能力会超过本地物种,或成为本地物种的猎物,破坏生态系统,例如佛罗里达埃弗莱德河流域的缅甸和大湖区的斑马贝类。",
  "What is a keystone species?": "什么是关键物种?",
  "A keystone species has a disproportionately large effect on its ecosystem relative to its abundance. Removing a keystone species causes significant changes throughout the food web. Classic examples include wolves in Yellowstone (top-down control of elk) and sea otters in kelp forests (controlling sea urchin populations).": "相对于其丰量而言,一个基石物种对其生态系统的影响特别大。 消除一个基石物种在整个食物网中造成了重大变化。 典型的例子包括黄石公园中的狼(对的上下控制)和海藻森林中的海燕(对海胆种群的控制 ) 。",
  "What is primary succession?": "初级继承是什么?",
  "Primary succession occurs on surfaces that have never supported life — bare rock, cooled lava, or retreating glaciers. Pioneer species like lichens and mosses colonize first, slowly breaking down rock into soil over centuries. The sequence progresses from lichens to mosses to grasses to shrubs to trees, eventually reaching a climax community.": "最初的继承发生在从未支撑生命的表面——裸露的岩石、冷却的熔岩或退缩的冰川。 原生物种,如地衣和苔,首先殖民,几个世纪以来慢慢地将岩石破碎到土壤中。 顺序从苔榈到草,再到灌木到树木,最终达到高潮社区。",
  "What is the greenhouse effect?": "温室效应是什么?",
  "The greenhouse effect is a natural process where certain atmospheric gases (CO₂, methane, water vapor, N₂O) absorb infrared radiation emitted by Earth's surface and re-radiate it, warming the atmosphere. Without it, Earth would be about 33°C colder. The enhanced greenhouse effect refers to the additional warming caused by human-produced increases in these gases.": "温室效应是一种自然过程,其中某些大气气体(CO2、甲烷、水蒸气、N2O)吸收了地球表面释放的红外线辐射,对地球进行再辐照,使大气层变暖。没有它,地球将更冷约33°C。强化的温室效应是指由人类生产的这些气体增加而增加的温室效应。",
  "What is an ecological footprint?": "什么是生态足迹?",
  "An ecological footprint measures the biologically productive land and water area needed to sustain a population's resource consumption and waste generation. It is compared to biocapacity — the available productive area. When footprint exceeds biocapacity, a population is running an ecological deficit, consuming resources faster than they regenerate.": "生态足迹衡量维持人口资源消耗和废物产生所需的生物生产土地和水区,与生物能力——现有生产区相比,当足迹超过生物能力时,人口正在出现生态赤字,消耗资源的速度超过其再生的速度。",
  "Indigenous communities in the Amazon use controlled burns, selective harvesting, and agroforestry. Studies show their territories harbor higher biodiversity than some national parks that exclude human activity. Approximately 80% of the world's remaining biodiversity exists on indigenous-managed lands. What conservation conclusion follows?": "研究显示,其领地的生物多样性高于某些排除人类活动的国家公园。 世界上大约80%的剩余生物多样性存在于土著管理的土地上。 接下来的养护结论是什么?",
  "Studies confirm that indigenous-managed lands harbor exceptional biodiversity. TEK includes fire management (preventing catastrophic buildup), rotational harvesting (allowing recovery), and polyculture agroforestry (maintaining habitat complexity). Conservation biology increasingly embraces co-management models that pair TEK with Western science. Excluding indigenous peoples from 'protected' areas can paradoxically reduce biodiversity.": "TEK包括火灾管理(防止灾难性集结 ) 、 轮捕(回收) 和 多种作物农林业(保持生境复杂性 ) 。 养护生物学越来越多地采用将TEK与西方科学结合起来的共同管理模式。 将土著人民排除在“受保护”地区之外可以减少生物多样性,这自相矛盾。"
}